#include<stdio.h>
#include<string.h>
/*
3
01-JAN-1900
10-JAN-1900
16-DEC-1900

Output:
Case 1: 1 Hundreds
Case 2: 10 Hundreds
Case 3: 50 Tens
*/

int main()
{
	int month[]= {0,31,59,90,120,151,181,212,243,273,304,334};
	int days,t,q=1;
	int dd, mm, yyyy;
	char mmm[4];
	scanf("%d",&t);
	while(t--){
	days=0;
	scanf("%d-%3s-%d", &dd, mmm, &yyyy);
	if (strcmp(mmm, "JAN") == 0)
		mm = 0;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "FEB") == 0)
		mm = 1;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "MAR") == 0)
		mm = 2;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "APR") == 0)
		mm = 3;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "MAY") == 0)
		mm = 4;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "JUN") == 0)
		mm = 5;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "JUL") == 0)
		mm = 6;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "AUG") == 0)
		mm = 7;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "SEP") == 0)
		mm = 8;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "OCT") == 0)
		mm = 9;
	else if (strcmp(mmm, "NOV") == 0)
		mm = 10;
	else
		mm = 11;
	
	days=dd+month[mm];
	
	if (mm>1 && yyyy % 4 == 0 && (yyyy % 100 != 0 || yyyy % 400 == 0))
		days=days+1;
	
	if (days <= 300)
		printf("Case %d: %d Hundreds\n", q++, days);
	else if (days <= 360)
		printf("Case %d: %d Tens\n", q++, days - 300);
	else
		printf("Case %d: %d Ones\n", q++, days - 360);
	}
	return 0;
}
